  "informal_statement": "The image of a finite set under a function has at most as many elements as the original set — applying a function can only merge elements, never create new ones.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Directly `Finset.card_image_le`.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem card_image_le' (s : Finset ℕ) (f : ℕ → ℕ) : (s.image f).card ≤ s.card",
